table_trans: If the candidate is unable to produce to the appointing authority the necessary and appropriate certificates for the scrutiny of the claim in the application made to the Commission, the candidate will not be appointed and the recommendation of the candidate will be automatically deemed to be void and so communicated to the Commission.

These Higher Grade Short-Recruits are being recommended on the basis of the provisions in the Government Circular, General Administration Department, dated 13.08.2014 and dated 19.12.2018 and other updated Government Decisions. Considering the suggestions made by the Government in this regard from time to time, the candidates who have been recommended for the posts of Parallel Reserved for Higher Grade Short-Recruits should be appointed to the post of Higher Grade Short-Recruits (Marathi / English) only after confirming and verifying before appointment on the basis of their school / college leaving evidence and other relevant documents that they are actually candidates from the open (Non-Recursive) category.

The candidates belonging to Backward Classes who have been recommended for the post of Open Category will be dealt with as per the instructions of the Department of Social Justice, Cultural Affairs and Special Assistance, Govt. Decision No.: CBC- 10/2004 Pr. र.570/म V, dated 16.5.2007.

The appointment authority is required to take action as per the instructions mentioned in the General Administration Department, Government Circular No: BCC-2012 / Q र.332/12/16-ब, dated 18.5.2013 regarding submission of caste validity certificate and procedure to be followed in case of invalidation of caste certificate in respect of candidates belonging to backward classes.

para_trans: Government Memorandum No: ASC 1524 / P.No.175 / Pr. 16.02.2026
Page 5 of 8
table_trans: The appointing authority shall also take steps to ensure that the caste claims (caste certificate and caste validity certificate) of all the recommended candidates are issued by the Director, Directorate of Social Welfare, Pune and the tribal claims (caste certificate and caste validity certificate) by the Commissioner, Tribal Research and Training Institute, Pune by the respective committee.

A candidate to be appointed by nomination to the post of Higher Secondary Short-story Writer is required to possess the requisite computer qualification as specified in the General Administration Department, Government Decision No: Training 2000 / Q र.61/2001/39, dated 19.3.2003, (a) D.O.E.A.C.C. certificate of passing any one of the official CCC or O level or B or C level examinations of the Society or (b) certificate of passing the official MS-CIT examination of the Maharashtra State Board of Higher and Technical Education, Mumbai, one of these certificates or the Government Decision No: Matans 2012 / Q र.277/39, dated 04.02.2013 and Government Supplementary No. 2012 / Q र.270/39, dated 08.01.2018. However, if the candidate does not possess this certificate / qualification at the time of acceptance of appointment, the candidate shall be required to submit the prescribed certificate of computer knowledge of the institution mentioned in the above decision within two years from the date of acceptance of appointment.

The candidates to be appointed to the post of Upper Class Shortwriter (English) are required to have passed the Board's Examination of Marathi Shortwriting 80 words per minute and Marathi Typewriting 30 words per minute within 4 years from the date of their entry into the Government Service as per Rules 3 & 4 of the Maharashtra Civil Service (Compulsory Examination of Marathi Shortwriting / Marathi Typewriting to be obtained by English Shortwriters and English Typewriters) Rules 1991. However, as per the provisions of Government Notification No. TELEP 2015 / PR र.176/भ No. 2, dated 24.03.2017, English Shortwriters who have held a Government Certificate of Marathi Short Writing and Marathi Typewriting 80 words per minute and Marathi Shortwriting 30 words per minute or more within a period of 4 years from the date of their original appointment or joining the Government Service, as the case may be, are required to have passed the Board's Examination of Marathi Typewriting 80 words per minute and Marathi Shortwriting 80 words per minute within 4 years from the date of their entry into the Government Service.

table_trans: Exemption from passing the exam will be granted.

As per the rules regarding Hindi and Marathi language examination, if the recommended candidate has not passed the examination earlier or is not exempted from passing the said examination, then such candidates will be required to pass the examination.

Testimonials have been sent to the candidates through the Maharashtra Public Service Commission. This test is to be completed and submitted by the candidate on his / her appearance in the allotted department / office. After receiving the testimonials from the candidates who have appeared, the pre-certification of the candidates should be done by the General Administration Department, Police Department taking into account the provisions of the Government Decision No: Chap 1008 / Q र.214/08/16-अ, dated 9.1.2009 and if the report is unfavourable, the concerned candidates should be immediately reported to this department in accordance with the instructions of the Government Decision on Government Circular No. Chap-1012 / Q र.63/16-अ, dated 26/08/2014. The order of appointment of the candidates should clearly mention that "the candidates who have been appointed have been superseded by the following order and the termination of service shall be done without prior notice."

The certificate of all Backward Class candidates other than Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes not falling in the Creamy Layer for the financial year 1.4.2022 to 31.3.2023 should be checked as per the instructions given under the Department of Social Justice, Cultural Affairs and Special Assistance, Government Circular No.: CBC- 10/2006 Q र.15/म QQ5, dated 30.6.2006 and in this regard, the provision prescribed under the Department of Social Justice and Special Assistance Government Decision No.: CBC- 10/2008 Q र.697/व JJBJ-1, dated 24.6.2013 should be considered.

Candidates may note that the Maharashtra Public Service Commission has recommended candidates from the waiting list of the Direct Service Higher Secondary Short-list (Marathi / English) Examination 2022 subject to final adjudication of the judicial case filed in various High Courts / High Tribunals regarding the issue of Common Reservation of Parallel Reservation as well as other issues.

The Maharashtra Public Service Commission has made the recommendations of the candidates based on the result of the original list of the examination presented by it to the Government subject to the condition that their eligibility in accordance with the claims made in the application for the examination presented by them be verified from the original certificate from the Government level before appointment. If the information given by the candidates in the application form is found to be false or incorrect or if the required certificates are not fulfilled as per the claim in the application form, the recommendation / candidature of the candidates concerned will be cancelled at any stage at the Government level while examining the claims or for any other reason as per the provision of the notification.

Copies of the identity card submitted at the time of the examination by the candidates who have been recommended from the waiting list of Higher Secondary Short Writer (Marathi / English) Examination 2022 are also being made available along with it. The application photo of the candidates concerned and whether the candidate is the same as the original candidate, the photo and signature of the candidate in the application form from the identity card provided by them at the time of examination, whether the photo and signature of the candidate in the identity card are of the same candidate, whether the identity card submitted is authentic, should be thoroughly checked at the government level before appointment. The validity of the identity card submitted by the candidates at the time of examination should be verified by the competent authorities concerned. Only after this, the appointment of candidates for the post of Higher Secondary Short Writer (Marathi / English) should be made.

In the case of candidates belonging to economically weaker section, the decision regarding their appointment should be taken after verification by the concerned authority before appointment in the prescribed format certified by the competent authority and the certificate of financial breakdown for the prescribed period.

As the thematic examination is of a stand-alone category, "shall remain in operation for one year from the date of declaration of result or until the date of further examination results, whichever is earlier" Please refer to the Government Circular No. 1119 / Q. र.115/8, dated 02/08/2019 of the General Administration Department, regarding instructions regarding the proceedings to be taken with regard to requisitioning of candidates in the waiting period.

The advertisement for the said examination had clarified that the posts of Higher Secondary Short Writer are in the Ministry Administrative Department and various Government offices in Brihanmumbai. As such, the request for posting of candidates to another district will not be entertained and the application in this regard will not be entertained. Also, the request for re-allocation to another department / office will not be entertained. As per the General Administration Department, Government Notification No. SRV 2016 / PR र.281/ब R, dated 21st June, 2021, the candidates are required to accept the application for extension of the candidates within the said period and the Department will not entertain any communication in this regard.
